## § Design System block (paste into every prompt)

DESIGN SYSTEM (REQUIRED — <one-line atmosphere, e.g. "dark scientific instrument: cockpit × IDE">; NOT a generic SaaS dashboard):
- Surfaces: background <#bg>; panels <#panel>; raised/hover <#raised>; hairline borders <rgba(...)>.
- Text: primary <#text>; secondary <#muted>. Never use a faint gray below 4.5:1 contrast for real text.
- ONE cool accent: <#accent> (selection, links, active data, focus rings) — calm, NOT neon, no outer glow.
- ONE warm accent reserved ONLY for <the AI/agent zone>: <#warm>.
- Status colors, always with icon + text label (never color alone): green <#ok> = ok/verified; amber <#warn> = warning; red <#bad> = error/failed.
- <Domain> colormap = <e.g. viridis> for any field/heat visual + its color bar.
- Type: <grotesk sans, NOT Inter> for prose; <JetBrains Mono> for ALL numbers/IDs/paths/data (tabular).
  Weight-driven hierarchy, restrained sizes, dense but calm.
- Radii: <6px> controls / <12px> containers. No shadow soup. Every number has units; status explicit;
  clean spatial separation; generous padding; subtle focus rings; no emojis.

## App shell (every screen shares this — describe in each prompt)
- TOP BAR: <brand + selector + interactive breadcrumb + global status chips>. NO pill/tab screen-switcher.
- LEFT (<width>): <primary navigation, e.g. an IDE-style collapsible tree; status rolls up to ancestors>.
- CENTER: <the focused object's workbench; changes by selection>.
- RIGHT (<width>): <inspector / AI-agent zone (warm accent), context line of the focused node>.

